    "However, Naïve Bayes is unsuitable for regression tasks and assumes feature independence, which can be advantageous when dealing with truly independent maturity indexes (Kusuma & Putra, 2018).",
    "KNN K-Nearest Neighbour (K-NN) is a versatile non-parametric machine learning approach suitable for handling large, multidimensional datasets in both classification and regression tasks.",
    "K-NN stores training dataset examples and classifies new instances based on their similarity to stored examples.",
    "The choice of k, the number of neighbours to consider during classification, impacts the method's performance (Lindon et al., 2011).",
    "A suitable \"k\" is determined through distance measures like Euclidean, Hamming, Manhattan, Minkowski, or Chebychev (Isa et al., 2017)."
  ],
